sentences: Bobby Previte (born July 16, 1951 in Niagara Falls, New York) is a drummer, composer, and bandleader.
Bobby Previte (born July 16, 1951 in Niagara Falls, New York) is a drummer, composer, and bandleader.
He moved to New York City in 1979 and began professional relationships with John Zorn, Wayne Horvitz, and Elliott Sharp.

A review of his 1988 album Claude's Late Morning reports that "Perhaps most striking is Previte's skill in composing music that fully integrates these disparate instruments — including drums and drum machine, electric guitar and keyboards, trombone, harp, accordion, banjo, pedal steel guitar, tuba, and harmonica — while emphasizing each instrument's unique, individual sound."
